message.content: The expression $(y-2)+(y-8)$ is defined for all real numbers $y.$ However, the function $\ell(y)=\frac{1}{(y-2)+(y-8)}$ is undefined when the denominator is equal to $0,$ so we cannot allow $y=2$ or $y=8.$ In interval notation, the domain of the function is $\boxed{(-\infty,2) \cup (2,8) \cup (8,\infty)}.$
